Signal.Description:
Struct sampled once per control loop containing:
- ultrasonic: { float distance_cm; uint32 timestamp_ms; bool valid; }
- ir: { bool left_flag; bool right_flag; uint32 timestamp_ms; bool valid; }
A frame is considered "valid for exploration start" if valid==true for ultrasonic and both IR flags are available.

Structured observation containing:
- position: current cell (row, col), heading
- face: {FRONT, LEFT, RIGHT}
- evidence: {PRESENT, ABSENT}
After consistency checks, GridMapModule converts this into classification updates for specific wall segments between neighboring cells.

struct SensorFrame {
  struct { float distance_cm; uint32 timestamp_ms; bool valid; } ultrasonic;
  struct { bool left_flag; bool right_flag; uint32 timestamp_ms; bool valid; } ir;
}
Provided once per control-loop cycle.

Data.Content:
Enumeration definitions:

- CellState (for cells):
  enum CellState { UNKNOWN = 0, FREE = 1, BLOCKED = 2 };

- WallState (for inter-cell walls):
  enum WallState { UNKNOWN = 0, PRESENT = 1, ABSENT = 2 };

- MissionState (top-level mission states, mirrored from FSM):
  enum MissionState { IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED };

- SecondRunStatusEnum:
  enum SecondRunStatus { SECOND_RUN_NOT_EXECUTED, SECOND_RUN_SUCCESS, SECOND_RUN_FAILURE };

- ReturnToStartStatusEnum:
  enum ReturnToStartStatus { RETURN_NOT_EXECUTED, RETURN_SUCCESS, RETURN_FAILURE };

- ExplorationEventType:
  enum ExplorationEventType { EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT };

- MotionMode:
  enum MotionMode { MOTION_EXPLORE, MOTION_RETURN, MOTION_SECOND_RUN };

- Heading:
  enum Heading { NORTH, EAST, SOUTH, WEST };

- AvoidanceManeuverType:
  enum AvoidanceManeuverType { AVOID_STOP_AND_TURN, AVOID_ARC_TURN };
